title: The Pee Pee Guy
desc: A business associate falls from grace, while Ray takes the fall for a mate. A chance meeting in the park and a new apprentice.

title: Unicorns Know Everybody's Name
desc: The wrong guy gets the good news and Unicorn's do exist. The first of a thousand kisses and good ole revenge.

title: Captain Obvious
desc: Anger mismanagement and no such thing as Jesus. If you can't kill your own brother-in-law, who can?

title: On Behalf of Society
desc: Ray doesn't like surprises, sit downs, sandwiches, or assholes. Brittany asks tough questions, while Ray hands out trouble to those that seek it.

title: Hard Worker
desc: People are not always what they appear to be and a good strong name is important. It's also important to lock your car when you leave it.

title: Your Mum's Got a Strongbox
desc: A nutritious breakfast is the key to good health. As is looking in the trunk before stealing a car. People say they do but does anybody really like surprises?

title: Shoulda Tapped
desc: Ray don't tap but he gives good advice. Sometimes you have to take the scenic route.

title: Don't Be a Dickhead
desc: Ray solves problems but under no circumstances does he answer questions.

title: I Came from Your Balls?
desc: Ray and Ally get caught out and good dental hygiene is as important as paying your debts.

title: Monsters
desc: Is there really any such thing as monsters?

title: Can't Save You
desc: All things must end, even Christmas.

title: Let Me Stop You There
desc: Lady troubles, old friends and hearts on trees.

title: Watch Out for Snakes
desc: Ray does favours but doesn't forgive.

title: See You in Your Dreams
desc: An old friend takes the fall and an associate pays for past misdeeds.

title: Socks Are Important
desc: When exiting a department store, make sure you don't leave with less than you came with.

title: Nice Face
desc: Enemies come and go and so, alas, do friends.

title: There Rust, and Let Me Die
desc: We live, no doubt, but does anybody really die?

title: Coulda Shoulda
desc: If your mistakes lead to your death, how can you learn from them?

title: Champ
desc: If you think violence is not the answer, you don't understand the question.

title: All I Ever Wanted
desc: You can't make anybody stay but you can sure as hell make 'em go.

title: Cut The Crap Princess
desc: Curiosity rarely kills the cat but too many pharmaceuticals generally will.

title: Before I Went To War
desc: All is fair in love and war but not in business. Forgiveness may be divine but revenge is way more fun.

title: Ray Who?
desc: Don't live in the past they say, but what if it's a hell of a lot better than the present?

title: I'm Your Girl
desc: Everybody loves a road trip.

title: I'll See You Soon
desc: There's a reason why the road less traveled, is less traveled.

title: I'm Not Leaving
desc: If nothing ends, what begins?
